 To tune resampling, the following issues are taken into account [8], [44]:

1
control of the diversity of the particles population;

2
avoidance of particles' impoverishment, i.e., avoidance of the absence of particles in the vicinity of the correct state;

3
selection of the optimal number of particles;

4
selection of the particles' subsets to be substituted (stratified resampling);

5
parallel implementation of resampling to improve the speed of the PF algorithm.

